# My agent foundation

This repo is my agent setup — the house rules, skills, and brand my agent runs on.
Clone it, run one command, and your agent works exactly like mine.

## Get set up (two commands)

```bash
git clone <this-repo-url> my-foundation
cd my-foundation
bash install.sh
```

Then restart your agent (or refresh the session). That's it — you're running my
foundation.

## What just got installed

- **`skills/`** → copied into your agent's skills directory (`~/.claude/skills/`).
  Additive — it never removes skills you already had.
- **`CLAUDE.md`** → installed as your agent's house rules. If you already had one,
  it was **backed up to `CLAUDE.md.bak`** first — nothing of yours is lost.
- **`brand/`** → placed where your agent can find it, so output sounds like our shop.

The installer prints exactly what it did. Options:

```bash
USE_SYMLINKS=1 bash install.sh          # symlink skills so `git pull` updates them live
CLAUDE_DIR=/path bash install.sh        # install into a different agent config dir
```

## Staying current

I improve this over time. To get the latest:

```bash
git pull
bash install.sh
```

An update is a pull — you never have to re-copy anything by hand.

## What's in here

```
CLAUDE.md      the house rules every run follows
skills/        the capabilities (one folder per skill)
brand/         the brand kit — voice, audience, style
install.sh     the installer you just ran
```

## Note

This repo holds **standards, not secrets** — no API keys, tokens, or client data.
If a skill needs a key to run, you'll set that up locally on your own machine; it's
never stored here.
